0Frances%20said%20of%20his%20decision%20to%20invest.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20also%20Israeli%2C%20and%20that%20was%20part%20of%20the%20thesis%20of%20the%20fund.%2090%25%20of%20all%20of%20my%20deals%20are%20with%20Israeli-related%20founders%20and%20teams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGroup%2011%20wasn't%20included%20in%20Navan's%20S-1%2C%20as%20the%20company's%20filing%20didn't%20include%20shareholders%20with%20a%20stake%20of%20less%20than%205%25%20who%20aren't%20represented%20on%20Navan's%20board%20and%20who%20didn't%20sell%20shares%20in%20the%20IPO.%20The%20firm%20shared%20the%20size%20of%20its%20stake%20with%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20%2420%20share%20price%2C%20Frances%20and%20Group%2011%20are%20sitting%20on%20a%20stake%20worth%20around%20%24122%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EH.%20Barton%20Asset%20Management%2C%20an%20investor%3A%3Cp%3EH.%20Barton%20Asset%20Management%20owns%203.1%20million%20Navan%20shares%2C%20or%201.2%25%20of%20the%20company%20after%20its%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20is%20helmed%20by%20Harrison%20Barton%2C%20the%20private%20equity%20investor%20and%20former%20offensive%20lineman%20for%20the%20San%20Francisco%2049ers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201999%2C%20the%20year%20after%20he%20left%20the%20NFL%2C%20Barton%20began%20investing%20in%20venture%20capital%20through%20his%20fund-of-funds%20Champion%20Ventures%2C%20later%20renamed%20HRJ%20Capital%2C%20which%20he%20cofounded%20alongside%20another%20former%20professional%20football%20player%2C%20Ronnie%20Lott.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20HRJ%20Capital%20was%20acquired%20by%20Capital%20Dynamics%20in%202009%2C%20Barton%20started%20H.%20Barton%20Asset%20Management%20to%20invest%20in%20early-stage%20tech%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarton%20sold%20121%2C635%20shares%20in%20Navan's%20IPO%2C%20which%20at%20a%20%2425%20share%20price%20would've%20netted%20his%20firm%20about%20%243%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20%2420%20a%20share%2C%20his%20remaining%20stake%20is%20worth%20about%20%2460%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMichael%20Sindicich%2C%20president%3A%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221310%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michael%20Sindicich%2C%20president%20of%20Navan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6902c5f60be9845f2dc55ce3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22983%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Sindicich%2C%20president%20of%20Navan.%3Cp%3ENavan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESindicich%20owns%20about%201.2%20million%20Navan%20shares%2C%20or%200.4%25%20of%20the%20company%20after%20its%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESindicich%20was%20appointed%20Navan's%20president%20in%20March.%20He%20began%20as%20a%20senior%20executive%20in%20Navan's%20sales%20department%20in%202016%20and%20worked%20his%20way%20up%20the%20ranks%20over%20the%20years%2C%20serving%20from%20April%202023%20until%20this%20March%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20Navan%20Expense%2C%20the%20company's%20expense%20management%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Navan%2C%20Sindicich%20led%20sales%20teams%20at%20Apptimize%2C%20acquired%20by%20Airship%2C%20and%20cofounded%20the%20financial%20brokerage%20Hurley%20Brothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESindicich%20sold%20about%20230%2C000%20shares%20in%20Navan's%20IPO.%20At%20%2425%20a%20share%2C%20that%20sale%20would've%20netted%20him%20about%20%245.8%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20%2420%20a%20share%2C%20his%20remaining%20stake%20is%20worth%20about%20%2420%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMichael%20Kourey%2C%20board%20director%3A%3Cp%3EKourey%20owns%20about%2061%2C000%20shares%20of%20Navan%2C%20or%20roughly%20.02%25%20of%20the%20company%20after%20its%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKourey%20has%20a%20long%20history%20in%20executive%20finance%20and%20auditing%20roles%2C%20most%20recently%20serving%20as%20Dialpad's%20CFO%20from%202021%20until%20this%20February.%20He%20joined%20Navan's%20board%20of%20directors%20in%20November%202024%20as%20its%20audit%20committee%20chair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Dialpad%2C%20Kourey%20briefly%20served%20as%20Okta's%20CFO%20in%20early%202021%2C%20where%20he'd%20sat%20on%20the%20board%20of%20directors%20for%20five%20years.%20He%20was%20also%20the%20CFO%20of%20software%20company%20Vlocity%2C%20acquired%20by%20Salesforce%20in%202020%3B%20the%20CFO%20of%20customer%20experience%20management%20company%20Medallia%3B%20and%20a%20partner%20at%20Khosla%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20earliest%20win%20came%20at%20Polycom%2C%20where%20he%20joined%20as%20the%20conferencing%20tech%20maker's%20seventh%20employee.%20He%20stayed%20there%20for%2020%20years%2C%20serving%20as%20Polycom's%20CFO%20for%2015%20years%20and%20leading%20the%20company%20through%20its%201996%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20his%20role%20on%20Navan's%20board%2C%20he%20also%20sits%20on%20the%20boards%20of%20Medable%2C%20Illumio%2C%20Ohalo%2C%20Dialpad%2C%20and%20Cribl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKourey%20didn't%20sell%20any%20shares%20in%20Navan's%20IPO.%20At%20a%20%2420%20share%20price%2C%20his%20remaining%20stake%20is%20worth%20about%20%241.2%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EClara%20Liang%2C%20board%20director%3Cp%3ELiang%20owns%20about%2057%2C000%20shares%20of%20Navan%2C%20or%20about%20.02%25%20of%20the%20company%20after%20its%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiang%20leads%20global%20strategic%20operations%20at%20fintech%20startup%20Stripe.%20She%20joined%20Navan's%20board%20of%20directors%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20known%20Cohen%20and%20Twig%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20having%20spent%20three%20years%20as%20the%20chief%20product%20officer%20of%20Jive%20Software%2C%20the%20then-public%20tech%20company%20that%20bought%20Cohen%20and%20Twig's%20first%20startup%2C%20StreamOnce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiang%20has%20also%20held%20product%20leadership%20roles%20at%20Airbnb%20and%20IBM.%20She%20currently%20sits%20on%20SoFi's%20board%20of%20directors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20didn't%20sell%20any%20shares%20in%20Navan's%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20%2420%20share%20price%2C%20Liang's%20rema